				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Incidentally, having an SEC immediately after a (not-taken) BCC instruction is indeed redundant - BCC only branches if carry is clear, so if it didn't branch then carry must be set. The fact that removing a single byte causes the problem to go away suggests that this is indeed a problem with trying to branch too far, but we'd need to see the entire program to be able to confirm that possibility.</div>

					
